SIMPLE: univocally
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Univocally
<hw>U*niv"o*cal*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a univocal manner; in
one term; in one sense; not equivocally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How is sin <qex>univocally</qex> distinguished into venial and
mortal, if the venial be not sin?</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Univocation</ent>⟦br⟧
